""" Pattern Matching Problem: Find All Occurrences of a Pattern in a String
In this problem, we ask a simple question: how many times can one string occur as a substring of another? Recall from “Find the Most Frequent Words in a String” that different occurrences of a substring can overlap with each other. 
For example, ATA occurs three times in CGATATATCCATAG
"""


def PATTERNMATCHING(genome,pattern):
    '''
    Pattern Matching Problem- page 13
    Find all occurrences of a pattern in a string
    takes a DNA string and a pattern and returns all starting positions in Genome where Pattern appears as a substring
    '''
    indices=[]
    k=len(pattern)
    for i in range(len(genome)-k):
        sub=genome[i:i+k].upper()
        if sub==pattern.upper():
            indices.append(i)
    return indices

def printArray(arr):
    '''
    takes an array and prints its elements
    '''
    s="";
    for i in arr:
        s=s+str(i)+"\t"
    print(s)


